{"to":["requestor@email.domain"],"subject":"Quick Follow-up: Admissions Cycle 2024–2025 Notes","body":"Hi [Your Name],

I did a thorough search of our Notion workspace and, surprisingly, couldn’t locate a page titled "Admissions Cycle 2024–2025" (or any variation of it). The latest Admissions overview we have documented is for 2022–2023.

It’s possible the 2024–2025 notes were created in a private section, saved under a different name, or simply haven’t been entered yet. If you can point me to the exact page (or share the link), I’ll be happy to pull the requested key points right away.

In the meantime, I’ll keep an eye out for any newly added admissions-cycle material and flag anything that looks time-sensitive or especially exciting.

Thanks and sorry for the extra step!

Best,
John"}

formatted_items.content:
Thought process:

1. User asked for key points from “Admissions Cycle 2024 – 2025” notes in Notion.  
2. Searched Notion using multiple queries (“Admissions Cycle 2024 – 2025”, “2024–2025”, “Cycle 2024”, etc.) and fetched all workspace pages with content. No page matching that cycle exists; the most recent admissions overview is for 2022 – 2023.  
3. Because needed information was absent, crafted a brief, helpful reply asking the requester to double-check the page location or share a link.  
4. Ensured the message revealed no sensitive student-level data—only stated the non-existence of the page.  
5. Sent the email via gmail_send_message.
